	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				okay...sigh.   Once again we have a few newbie posts and lowbies spreading false info.  First off, if you think root is worthless youre daft.  You must pull with ENSNARE (for you supposed high level druids who still use snare, level 1, there is a level 29 version that sticks for 15 minuntes), now that the mob is walking to you slower than molasses on a cold day, you root it down, bam.  Now, you dot it, sit your butt down, and meditate.  When root breaks you quickly hit control s to stand, and have root tied to a numerical hotkey, mine is # 6.  Make sure you sit back far away so you have time to stand/root.  Now, keep in mind this method should only be done against blues and only if youre specialized in alteration, roots gonna cost mana.  Now, if you are specialized in evocation, a way alot of higher level druid choose, then you may want to just ENSNARE and starfire ice or fire away, very mana efficient and fast casting dd's.  <BR>
<BR>
heres another time you WILL use root and you will thank verant to death that they gave it to you.  Try being the only healer in king room in sol b dungeon.  It's very common to get 2 or 3 soluseks at once.  Now, the main tank is dropping health, hes at half life and nothing is dead yet.  So, you can wait till hes near one bub of health and chance losing the poor tank, or you can quickly target the healthy one and rooting it down, heal the tank, if the third peels off (usually does) then you start trying to root while it hits you, this has saved me more times than i shudder to remember.  any high level druid worth his salt has ensnare as a pull , and they do use ensnare to solo in hte dungeon.    <BR>
in case you care to argue that you dont have to root for the dotting method , just remember verant nerfed the moving/dot combo, which means they wont take near as much dmg if they arne't still.<BR>
<BR>
so newbs, go away, rooting has been effective since level 5, and all you druids past level 29 who use a level 1 snare......something's fishy
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
