				I wish people would stop comparing root and snare, they're two completely different things. Snare is used for kiting, which is good experience at lower levels when we don't get as many dots, and root is for root/dot method. I suppose that if i could still find yellow and red cons as i could at lvl 30, kiting might be good experience. However, the higher you go, it seems that root/dot gets more mana efficient, especially with some of the better dots we get. Also, when you begin hunting in indoor zones such as lower guk and sol b, root becomes much more useful than snare. not only can you solo, but it keeps mobs off you and your group when you run to the zone.<BR>
<BR>
-Merenya Diamonddew, <BR>
